  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2018-10-11T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Modernizing Disclosures for Investors Act \n\nThis bill directs the Securities and Exchange Commission to: (1) report on the costs and benefits of requiring reporting companies to use Form 10-Q to satisfy quarterly financial disclosure requirements; and (2) make recommendations for decreasing costs, increasing transparency, and increasing efficiency of quarterly financial reporting by emerging growth companies."
